         <hazardstatement type="caution" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">REDUNDANCY LOST</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">If the manual bypass is in position 1 it is not possible
for the system to automatically switch to the inverter or static switch
if the supply from the bypass is lost.</howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The load is directly supplied
from the bypass. The manual bypass switch is bypassing the static
switch. The system will stay in bypass output mode until the position
of the manual bypass switch manually changes to another. No automatic
transfer is possible from this mode.</p>
